						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1461, Vikāri, Pushya, śu. 1,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1539 December 11 Thursday</hi> (not verifiable), in the reign of <hi rend="bold">Achyutadēva-Mahārāya.</hi> It records that <hi rend="bold">Achyutarāya-Mallapaṇṇa</hi> made a gift of the toll-revenue on garden produce amounting to <hi rend="italic">varāhas</hi> 1050 in <hi rend="bold">Doravadi-Sōmalāpura,</hi> a <hi rend="italic">mānya</hi> village belonging to the god Raghunāthadēva in <hi rend="bold">Vardādēvi-Ammana-paṭṭana,</hi> for the service of the god. </p>						

						</summary>
